<subSubSection id="899C42AEFF87FFB612FA7D56FDDAF8F7" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" type="description">
<paragraph id="C1391125FF87FFB612FA7D56FE3AFC7B" blockId="1.[151,1436,837,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="F3F2CD37FF87FFB612FA7D56FE8FFC83" bold="true" box="[151,324,837,862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Redescription.</emphasis>
Dorsal colour mostly opaque green, usually with black markings on head, face, pronotum, forewing and other parts of body showing variable degrees of sexual dimorphism, female usually with reduced black markings (Plate I: A–H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1391125FF87FFB612AA7DA2FF79FB1B" blockId="1.[151,1436,837,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Head slightly broader than pronotum; crown broad and short, blunt-roundish produced, somewhat flat with transverse discal furrow, not rounded at meeting line with frons but comparatively sharp angled; coronal suture distinct; ocelli in fore margin distant from eyes by about their own diameter (Plate I: A–G). Face broad; anteclypeus tapered; frontoclypeus moderately broadening dorsad; ocellocular area rather broad (Plate I: H). Pronotum broad, sides parallel (Plate I: A–G). Forewing long; appendix distinct, extended around wing apex; four apical cells and two closed subapical cells, outer triangular and much shorter and smaller than central, clavus with two veins, marginal vein complete in hind wing, first cubitus bifurcate and vannal veins 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB616017A99FBB1FB7F" box="[1132,1146,1162,1186]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB616C27A99FB76FB7F" box="[1199,1213,1162,1186]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.0">2</number>
separate (Plate I: I– J).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1391125FF87FFB612AA7AC2FD44FAA7" blockId="1.[151,1436,837,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Profemur setal row AV with 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB610627AC1FD9FFB37" box="[527,596,1234,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12</number>
similar peglike setae; AM 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB611EB7AC1FC44FB37" box="[902,911,1234,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="1.0">1</number>
present (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB611947AC2FB9FFB37" box="[1017,1108,1233,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. A" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1561,1583]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,201,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1418,193,1521]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: front femur, anterior view; B – C: left front tibia, upside view; D: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; E: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); F: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV). A – B &amp; D – F: N. cincticeps; C: N. malayanus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB616437AC2FBF7FB37" box="[1070,1084,1233,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Foretibia dorsal macrosetal formula 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB612967AE5FEC2FAD3" box="[251,265,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB613747AE5FEECFAD3" box="[281,295,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="4.0">4</number>
or 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB613387AE6FEA8FAD3" box="[341,355,1269,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="6.0">6</number>
+ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6131E7AE6FE4AFAD3" box="[371,385,1269,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB613F87AE6FE2CFAD3" box="[405,487,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. A" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1561,1583]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,201,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1418,193,1521]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: front femur, anterior view; B – C: left front tibia, upside view; D: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; E: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); F: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV). A – B &amp; D – F: N. cincticeps; C: N. malayanus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB613B47AE6FE2CFAD3" box="[473,487,1269,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
B–C). 
<collectingCountry id="B99151B5FF87FFB6105B7AE6FDA5FAD3" box="[566,622,1269,1294]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur setal formula 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB611067AE5FCB1FAD3" box="[875,890,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB611E67AE5FC51FAD3" box="[907,922,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB611C67AE5FC7EFAD3" box="[939,949,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB611A57AE6FBC4FAD3" box="[968,1039,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. A" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1561,1583]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,201,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1418,193,1521]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: front femur, anterior view; B – C: left front tibia, upside view; D: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; E: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); F: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV). A – B &amp; D – F: N. cincticeps; C: N. malayanus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6166C7AE6FBC4FAD3" box="[1025,1039,1269,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
D). 
<collectingCountry id="B99151B5FF87FFB616527AE6FBBCFAD3" box="[1087,1143,1269,1294]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia setal row AD with approximately 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6132E7B09FE94FAEF" box="[323,351,1306,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="10.0">10</number>
long stout setae and 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB610317B0AFD4DFAEF" box="[604,646,1305,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="0.0">0–5</number>
shorter setae between each long seta (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB616267B0AFB5BFAEF" box="[1099,1168,1305,1330]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. A" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1561,1583]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,201,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1418,193,1521]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: front femur, anterior view; B – C: left front tibia, upside view; D: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; E: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); F: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV). A – B &amp; D – F: N. cincticeps; C: N. malayanus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB616EF7B0AFB5BFAEF" box="[1154,1168,1305,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
E); pecten with several normal macrosetae and 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB613C97B2DFE79FA8B" box="[420,434,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.0">2</number>
platellae; PD with approximately 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6115A7B2DFCA5FA8B" box="[823,878,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="10.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="9.0">9–11</number>
macrosetae, 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6166E7B2DFBE7FA8B" box="[1027,1068,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="1.0" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.0">0–2</number>
shorter setae between each long seta, hardly as long as those of AD (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB610417B72FDA4FAA7" box="[556,623,1377,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. A" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1561,1583]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,201,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1418,193,1521]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. A: front femur, anterior view; B – C: left front tibia, upside view; D: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; E: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); F: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV). A – B &amp; D – F: N. cincticeps; C: N. malayanus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6100C7B72FDA4FAA7" box="[609,623,1377,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1391125FF87FFB612AA7B96FDF4F963" blockId="1.[151,1436,837,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Pygofer heavily sclerotized, side lobe usually with one or more thickened and modified macrosetae near apex, no appendage (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB613267BBAFE61FA1F" box="[331,426,1449,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="26.[151,249,1788,1810]" captionTargetBox="[183,1432,250,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[170,1456,241,1725]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nephotettix virescens (Distant). A – E: male pygofer side, lateral view; F: valve, ventral view; G – H: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226703/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB613E27BB9FE61FA1F" box="[399,426,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E); anal tube broad, nearly reaching apex of pygofer, heavily sclerotized ventrally, weakly sclerotized dorsally; valve short, broad triangular (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB6114E7BDEFCADFA3B" box="[803,870,1485,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[175,1416,200,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1424,193,1602]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – G: male pygofer side, lateral view; H: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226687/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6113A7BDDFCADFA3B" box="[855,870,1486,1510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
H); subgenital plate triangular, heavily sclerotized, macrosetae usually uniseriate (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB613957BE2FD8DF9D7" box="[504,582,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1760,1782]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,201,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[165,1414,193,1708]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – E: subgenital plate, ventral view; F – L: style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226688/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB610577BE1FD8DF9D7" box="[570,582,1522,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E); style well-developed, apophysis long and rather thick (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB617607BE2FA90F9D7" box="[1293,1371,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1760,1782]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,201,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[165,1414,193,1708]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – E: subgenital plate, ventral view; F – L: style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226688/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB617227BE1FA90F9D7" box="[1359,1371,1522,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F–L), preapical angle of style below apophysis sharply triangularly elongate (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB611A37806FBD6F9F3" box="[974,1053,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1760,1782]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,201,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[165,1414,193,1708]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – E: subgenital plate, ventral view; F – L: style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226688/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6167D7805FBD6F9F3" box="[1040,1053,1558,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F–L); connective long, Y-shaped, with anterior arms separate anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB61024782AFD51F98F" box="[585,666,1593,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,204,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[175,1411,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 12. Nephotettix malayanus Ishihara &amp; Kawase. A – F: aedeagus, ventral view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226698/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Fig. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB610107829FD51F98F" box="[637,666,1594,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
G); aedeagus with large basal socle (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB6165F782AFB4BF98F" box="[1074,1152,1593,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,199,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[173,1409,193,1880]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – C: aedeagus, ventral view; D: connective, dorsal view; E – I: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226689/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6161C7829FB4BF98F" box="[1137,1152,1594,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E–I), shaft robust, arising from hinge-like joint at ventral part of socle, slightly curved dorsad, with pair of lateral processes and, in most species, on dorsal surface elongate sclerotised carinae with variable numbers of spines directed distad (
<figureCitation id="59BD0DA0FF87FFB617787892FAA8F947" box="[1301,1379,1665,1690]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,199,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[173,1409,193,1880]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nephotettix cincticeps (Uhler). A – C: aedeagus, ventral view; D: connective, dorsal view; E – I: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226689/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Figs. 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB617397891FAA8F947" box="[1364,1379,1666,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E–I); gonopore subapical on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1391125FF87FFB612AA78DAFDDAF8F7" blockId="1.[151,1436,837,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
First valvula dorsal sculpturing granulose to maculose, submarginal for most of length (Plate VII: G–H). Second valvula abruptly broadened ~ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6102B78FEFD98F8DB" box="[582,595,1773,1798]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="774E0302FF87FFB6103178FEFDA2F8DB" box="[604,617,1773,1798]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" value="5.0">5</number>
its length from base, with small obliquely triangular dorsal teeth over nearly apical half (Plate VII: I–J).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
